The paper deals with Multi-Objective Games (MOGs) and proposes a co-evolutionary approach with memetics to improve convergence characteristics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the use of memetics and local solution refinements indicates a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves optimization and search techniques, which are relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of co-evolutionary approaches suggests a possible connection to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
